---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Doghouse Cafe"
  description="A community for real-world engineering stories, production failures, weird edge cases, and debugging paths."
  bodyClass="home-page"
>
  <img class="logo" src="/assets/img/doghouse-logo.png" alt="Doghouse Cafe logo" />

  <h1>Doghouse Cafe</h1>

  <p class="tagline">
    Where systems fail - and people figure out why.
  </p>

  <p class="description">
    Doghouse Cafe is a community for real-world engineering stories:
    production failures, weird edge cases, debugging paths, partial answers,
    and the messy gap between &ldquo;it should work&rdquo; and what actually happens.
  </p>

  <div class="actions">
    <a class="button primary" href="https://community.doghouse.cafe">Join the Community</a>
    <a class="button secondary" href="/blog/">Read the Blog</a>
  </div>

  <p class="note">
    Real experience &gt; polished writing. If it should work... but doesn&rsquo;t, it belongs here.
  </p>



<section class="home-about">
  <div class="about-grid">

    <div class="about-card">
      <h2>What this is</h2>
      <p>
        Dog House Cafe is a community for builders, operators, and debuggers who care about what actually happens in production—not just what should happen.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="about-card">
      <h2>What belongs here</h2>
      <p>
        Production failures, weird edge cases, partial fixes, and the paths people took to figure things out when systems didn’t behave the way they were supposed to.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="about-card">
      <h2>Why it exists</h2>
      <p>
        Most systems don’t fail randomly—they fail under pressure. This is a place to capture those moments and learn from them.
      </p>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>
</BaseLayout>
